quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  4,163,"We have indeed revealed to you as We revealed to Noah and the prophets after him, and [as] We revealed to Abraham and Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and the Tribes, Jesus and Job, Jonah, Aaron, and Solomon—and We gave David the Psalms—"
  4,164,and apostles We have recounted to you earlier and apostles We have not recounted to you—and to Moses Allah spoke directly—
  4,165,"apostles, as bearers of good news and warners, so that mankind may not have any argument against Allah, after the [sending of the] apostles; and Allah is all-mighty, all-wise"
  4,166,"But Allah bears witness to what He has sent down to you—He sent it down with His knowledge—and the angels bear witness [too], and Allah quite suffices as witness"
  4,167,"Indeed those who are faithless and bar [others] from the way of Allah, have certainly strayed into far error"
  4,168,"Indeed those who are faithless and do wrong, Allah shall never forgive them, nor shall He guide them to any way"
  4,169,"except the way to hell, to remain in it forever, and that is easy for Allah"
  4,170,"O mankind! The Apostle has certainly brought you the truth from your Lord. So have faith! That is better for you. And if you are faithless, [you should know that] to Allah indeed belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth, and Allah is all-knowing, all-wise"